property.label: Python Class
property.description: Python module used when creating a new device instances.

property.label: Production State Threshold
property.description: Production state threshold at which to start monitoring boxes.

property.label: If Description
property.description: Shows the interface description field in the interface list.

property.label: SNMP Communities
property.description: Array of SNMP community strings that ZenModeler uses when collecting SNMP information. When you set this property, communities are tried in order; the first in the list that is successful is used as zSnmpCommunity. If none is successful, then the current value of zSnmpCommunity is used. The default value for the entire system is "public."

property.label: SNMP Community String
property.description: Community string to be used when collecting SNMP information. If it is different than what is found by ZenModeler, it will be set on the modeled device.

property.label: SNMP Port
property.description: Port that the SNMP agent listens on.

property.label: SNMP Version
property.description: SNMP version used. Valid values are v1, v2c, v3.

property.label: SNMP Tries
property.description: Amount of tries to collect SNMP data

property.label: SNMP Timeout
property.description: Timeout time in seconds for an SNMP request

property.label: SNMP Engine ID
property.description: Engine ID is the administratively unique identifier for the SNMPv3 engine

property.label: SNMP Security Name
property.description: The Security Name (user) to use when making SNMPv3 requests.

property.label: SNMP Auth Password
property.description: The shared private key used for authentication. Must be at least 8 characters long.

property.label: SNMP Private Password
property.description: The shared private key used for encrypting SNMP requests. Must be at least 8 characters long.

property.label: SNMP Auth Type
property.description: Use "MD5" or "SHA" signatures to authenticate SNMP requests

property.label: SNMP Priv Type
property.description: "DES" or "AES" cryptographic algorithms.

property.label: SNMP Context
property.description: Defines the SNMPv3 CONTEXT specified by the -n flag

property.label: SNMP Collection Interval
property.description: Defines, in seconds, how often the system collects performance information for each device.

property.label: Router Map Collect Only (Local)
property.description: Only collect local routes. (These usually are manually configured rather than learned through a routing protocol.)

property.label: Route Map Collect Only (Indirect)
property.description: Only collect routes that are directly connected to the device.

property.label: Route Map Max Routes
property.description: Maximum number of routes to model.

property.label: Interface Map Ignore Types
property.description: Filters out interface maps that should not be discovered.

property.label: Interface Map Ignore Names
property.description: Filters out interfaces that should not be discovered.

property.label: Interface Map Ignore Description
property.description: Filters out interfaces based on description.

property.label: File System Map Ignore Types
property.description: Do not use.

property.label: File System Map Ignore Names
property.description: Sets a regular expression of file system names to ignore.

property.label: File System Size Offset
property.description: SNMP typically reports the total space available to privileged users. Resource Manager (like the df command) reports capacity based on the space available to non-privileged users. The value of zFileSystemSizeOffset should be the fraction of the total space that is available to non-privileged users. The default reserved value is 5% of total space, so zFileSystemSizeOffset is preset to .95. If the reserved portion is different than 5%, then adjust the value of zFileSystemSizeOffset accordingly. The fraction should be set according to the value ( Used + Avail ) / Size when the df -PkH command is run at the command line.

property.label: Hard Disk Map Match
property.description: Regular expression that uses the disk ID in the diskstats output to filter disk activity statistics for inclusion in performance monitoring.

property.label: IP Service Map Max Port
property.description: Specifies the highest port to scan. The default is 1024.

property.label: Device Templates
property.description: Sets the templates associated with this device. Linked by name.

property.label: Local Interface Names
property.description: Regular expression that uses interface name to determine whether the IP addresses on an interface should be incorporated into the network map. For instance, a loopback interface "lo" might be excluded.

property.label: Ignore SNMP Monitor?
property.description: Whether or not to ignore monitoring SNMP on a device.

property.label: Ignore Ping Monitor?
property.description: Whether or not to ping the device.

property.label: Status Connection Timeout (seconds)
property.description: The amount of time that the zenstatus daemon should wait before marking an IP service down.

property.label: Collector Client Timeout (seconds)
property.description: Allows you to set the timeout time of the collector client in seconds

property.label: Collector Decoding
property.description: Converts incoming characters to Unicode.

property.label: Username
property.description: Specifies the user name to use when performing command collection and SSH.

property.label: Password
property.description: Specifies the password to use when performing command logins and SSH.

property.label: Command Protocol
property.description: Establishes the protocol to use when performing command collection. Possible values are SSH and telnet.

property.label: Command Port
property.description: Specifies the port to connect to when performing command collection.

property.label: Command Login Tries
property.description: Sets the number of times to attempt login.

property.label: Timeout for Login (seconds)
property.description: Specifies the time to wait for a login prompt.

property.label: Timeout for Commands (seconds)
property.description: Specifies the time to wait for a command to complete.

property.label: Timeout for User Commands (seconds)
property.description: Specifies the time to wait for a user command to complete.

property.label: Command Search Path
property.description: Sets the path to search for any commands.

property.label: Command Path
property.description: Sets the default path where ZenCommand plug-ins are installed on the local Resource Manager box (or on a remote box where SSH is used to run the command).

property.label: Telnet Login
property.description: Regular expression to match the login prompt.

property.label: Telnet Password Regex
property.description: Regular expression to match the password prompt.

property.label: Telnet Success Regex
property.description: List of regular expressions to match the command prompt.

property.label: Enable Telnet?
property.description: When logging into a Cisco device issue the enable command to enable access during command collection.

property.label: Telnet Enable Regex
property.description: Regular expression to match the enable prompt.

property.label: Telnet Term Length
property.description: On a Cisco device, set term length to Zero.

property.label: Telnet Prompt Timeout (seconds)
property.description: Time to wait for the telnet prompt to return.

property.label: Key Path
property.description: Sets the path to the SSH key for device access.

property.label: Max OID Per Request
property.description: Sets the maximum number of OIDs to be sent by the SNMP collection daemons when querying information. Some devices have small buffers for handling this information so the number should be lowered.

property.label: Links
property.description: Specifies a place to enter any links associated with the device.

property.label: Icon Path
property.description: Specifies the icon to represent the device wherever device icon is shown, such as on the network map and device status page.

property.label: Log Collector Changes?
property.description: Indicates whether to log changes.

property.label: Enable Password
property.description: Enable password for Cisco routers

property.label: Nmap Port Scan Options
property.description: Options used on nmap when scanning ports. Used in IpServiceMap

property.label: SSH Concurrent Sessions
property.description: How many SSH sessions to open up to one device (some SSH servers have a limit)

property.label: Connection Information
property.description: Used by ZenPack authors to denote which zProperties comprise the credentials for this device class.
